.name
ScienceDemos
.description
Some science demos.  Sidereal is a tutorial program which introduces the
user to the relationships between Julian and calendar dates and solar and
sidereal times.  J2000 is a utility program which converts stellar
positions, proper motion, parallax and radial velocity from the standard
epoch B1950 (FK4) to epoch J2000 (FK5).  Galilean is a tutorial program
which determines the position of the Galilean satellites relative to
Jupiter.  Programs courtesy of David Eagle at Science Software. 
